Adaptive Execution

Graduated Authority (3 paths)

→

Three-tier processing adapts to each event’s needs. If AI is unavailable, Tier 1 rules still handle 60–70%. If a system is down, events queue safely. No single point of failure.

"Delegation should dynamically adapt to environmental shifts and failures"

Our Implementation:

🔎

Structural Transparency

Monitoring + ReAct traces

→

Every decision logged: why the Orchestrator routed where, which rule matched, what the AI agent observed→thought→acted. Full audit trail from event to outcome.

"Strictly enforced auditability via monitoring and verifiable task completion"

Our Implementation:

🔒

Permission Handling

Agent Access Model

→

Bank Teller model: agents read event data and Knowledge Base. No direct database writes. Actions execute through approved FastAPI services. Humans are always final authority.

"Least privilege, just-in-time access, semantic constraints on operations"

Our Implementation:

🛡️

Systemic Resilience

Graceful Degradation

→

Graceful degradation: AI down → rules process. Rules down → events queue. LLM-agnostic (swap providers). Learning Loop reduces AI dependency over time.

"Prevent cascading disruptions from cognitive monoculture or single points of failure"

